\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Ownership and Consent to Monitoring
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
County Property
\series default
:
 All County IT resources,
 including hardware,
 software,
 and data created,
 stored,
 or transmitted upon them,
 are the sole property of Elko County regardless of physical location or funding source,
 as defined and classified under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (IT Asset Management Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
No Expectation of Privacy
\series default
:
 Users shall have no expectation of privacy in County IT resources.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Consent to Monitoring
\series default
:
 Use of County IT resources constitutes consent to monitoring,
 logging,
 and disclosure for operational,
 security,
 legal,
 and investigative purposes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
System Use Notification
\series default
:
 The system use notification banner implementing NIST SP 800-53 Rev.
 5 AC-8 shall be displayed on County systems as specified in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Access Control Policy) to provide continuous notice of monitoring and consent.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Identity and Credentials
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Credential Protection
\series default
:
 Users shall not share passwords,
 tokens,
 or access badges.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Account Sharing
\series default
:
 Users shall not use another user's account or allow another person to use their account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Workstation Security
\series default
:
 Users shall lock their workstation or device whenever it is left unattended.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Acceptable Use Standards
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Official Use
\series default
:
 County IT resources are provided to support the official business of Elko County.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Incidental Personal Use
\series default
:
 Users may engage in limited personal use of County IT resources only during break and lunch periods,
 provided such use complies with the prohibitions defined in Section 6.4 of this policy,
 incurs no cost to the County,
 and does not delay or prevent the completion of assigned tasks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Prohibited Activities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Unauthorized Software
\series default
:
 Users shall not install unauthorized software on County IT resources.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Security Control Bypass
\series default
:
 Users shall not disable,
 circumvent,
 or tamper with security controls,
 including but not limited to endpoint protection software,
 firewalls,
 and logging mechanisms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Network Filter Evasion
\series default
:
 Users shall not use anonymization tools,
 proxies,
 or any other mechanism to bypass County network filters or monitoring.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
External AI Data Exposure
\series default
:
 Users shall not input Confidential or Restricted County data,
 as classified under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Data Governance and Classification Policy),
 into any Generative Artificial Intelligence (GenAI) system or Large Language Model (LLM) that is not a County-managed service.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Political and Commercial Use
\series default
:
 Users shall not use County IT resources for political campaigning,
 lobbying,
 or personal commercial ventures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prohibited Content
\series default
:
 Users shall not access,
 store,
 or distribute harassing,
 discriminatory,
 or sexually explicit content using County IT resources.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Reporting Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Security Incidents
\series default
:
 Users shall report suspected security incidents to Information Operations immediately upon discovery,
 and no later than one (1) hour after discovery.
 Intake handling is governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Lost or Stolen CJI-Capable Devices
\series default
:
 Users shall report any device capable of accessing Criminal Justice Information (CJI) that is lost,
 stolen,
 or otherwise unaccounted for to Information Operations no later than one (1) hour after discovery.
 This window supports the CJIS Security Policy v6.0 Section IR-6 Part (a) internal reporting clock operationalized in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Lost or Stolen General Assets
\series default
:
 Users shall report all other lost or stolen County IT resources to Information Operations no later than the end of the next business day after discovery.
 Losses of resources known or suspected to contain Confidential or Restricted County data shall be reported under the Security Incidents provision above.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exclusion
\series default
:
 Routine violations of this policy that do not involve a suspected security incident or Indicator of Compromise as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 shall be handled through the enforcement pathway established in Section 4 of this policy,
 and shall not be routed as Chapter 4 incidents solely on the basis of policy non-compliance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Acknowledgment Requirement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prerequisite
\series default
:
 Users shall execute the Acceptable Use Policy Acknowledgment,
 maintained in the System of Engagement,
 prior to being granted access to County IT resources.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Annual Refresh
\series default
:
